ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Miscellaneous comments on study, interview, methodology relevant to this form data
T2 SVR visual check quality score
Notes: The values are between 0-4 (includes decimal values). The value -999 will be present when data are not available.

ElementDescription: T1 SVR visual check quality score
Notes: The values are between 0-4 (includes decimal values). The value -999 will be present when data are not available.

ElementDescription: DrawEM_17 labels visual check quality score
Notes: The values are between 0-2 (includes decimal values). The value -999 will be present when data are not available.

ElementDescription: Age of the fetus (i.e., gestational age) in days
Type of gestational age used for fetal_age
Notes: 1 = Postovulatory gestational age, defined as days since the last ovulation, expected term of 266 days; 2 = Postmenstrual gestational age, days since the last menstrual period, expected term of 280 days
